<dl id="n12207l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12207l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12207l"> 207(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 10 without saying 1 / 2 goats, hen</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;hy&egrave;ne r&eacute;fl&eacute;chit un peu et dit: &ldquo;Si je compte jusqu&apos;au terme de dix sans avoir dit un, j&apos;aurai de la viande?&rdquo; Ils dirent: &ldquo;Tu <font color="green">[en]</font> auras.&rdquo; Elle dit: &ldquo;Deux ch&egrave;vres et <font color="green">[une]</font> poule, regardez si <font color="green">[cela]</font> ne fait pas dix <font color="green">[pattes]</font>.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[The hyena thought for a while and said: &ldquo;If I can count to ten without saying one, can I have the meat?&rdquo; They said: &ldquo;You can.&rdquo; She said: &ldquo;<mark>Two goats and a chicken, see if together they don&apos;t have ten feet</mark>.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 170 (from Chapter XXII, <i>Jeux d&apos;Esprit</i>, a collection of riddles)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
